### Brush Cleaning Services, Mackenzie River, Northwest Territories
#### Solicitation Number: 30002205
#### Closing Date: June 28, 2023, 2:00 p.m. Eastern Daylight Saving Time (EDT)

Fisheries and Oceans Canada is seeking Standing Offers from qualified contractors for Brush Cleaning Services along the Mackenzie River. The Department requires a maximum of three (3) contractors to provide services to various Fixed Aids to Navigation Sites on the Mackenzie River.

#### Scope ofWork

The scope of work includes:

* Mobilization to Sites
* Removal of Brush
* Stockpiling of felled timber at the limits of the works
* Demobilization

#### Technical Requirements

To be considered for this opportunity, contractors must meet the following mandatory technical criteria:

* Be registered with the Workers Safety and Compensation Commission of the Northwest Territories and Nunavut
* Possess a valid Business License Number to operate within the NWT and Nunavut
* Have a Contractor's Safety Plan

#### Contracting Authority

Bassam El-Daya
Senior Procurement Officer
Fisheries and Oceans Canada
Procurement Services and Procurement Hub

#### Compliance Requirements

This procurement is subject to the following Comprehensive Land Claims Agreements (CLCA):

* Gwich’in Comprehensive Land Claims Agreement
* Inuvialuit Final Agreement
* Sahtu Dene and Metis Comprehensive Land Claims Agreement
* Tlicho Land Claims Agreement

#### Travel and Living Expenses

Canada will not pay for travel or living expenses associated with performing the Work.

#### Security Requirements

There are no security requirements for this Standing Offer contract.

#### Notice URL

Please visit [Canada Buy and Sell](https://canadabuys.canada.ca/) for details and appendices.

#### Appendices
[stands available as attachments]

This entry should be published in both English and French in Gazette or on Government of Canada Tendering Website. It should be under relevant category and available to all federal and Territorial government employees.
